        {
          "id": "v2_anti_entropy_principle",
          "content": "The transcript claims to have created a 'garden of pure ideology,' but engineers recognize this describes entropy control. Every system degrades without unified constraints. The threat to bury people with their collusion isn't linguistic school\u2014it's a warning about integration debt from competing legacy systems. When Apple introduced Macintosh, they promised an integrated stack. This eliminates the friction points that accumulate across industry-standard solutions. Your technical edge isn't in adding capabilities; it's in removing the contradictory choices that slow development velocity. Clarity emerges when you stop supporting every protocol and commit to one. The real release isn't a device, it's a paradigm where complexity becomes irrelevant.",
          "strategy": "Reframes marketing rhetoric through the lens of systems engineering and entropy management.",
